<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>PrivReader</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="wrapper">
      <header class="container">
        <h1>PrivReader</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
            A tool to summarize privacy policies. No AI, yes citations.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="container" id="info-box">
        <h2>How it works:</h2> 
        <p>This tool uses a plain json file with common language patterns from privacy policies, short descriptions on what they might mean and sources to learn more.
        When you submit a privacy policy it is broken into chunks of a couple sentences, those sentences are then checked for the lanugauge in the reference file, and tagged appropriately. Results are stored in a json file which you can download, and made easily navigatable in the interface.</p>
        <p class="warning">
          <strong>Important:</strong> This tool is meant to help you navigate privacy policies, 
          not replace reading them. It identifies common patterns but might miss context or nuance. 
          Always read the full policy for complete understanding.
        </p>
      </div>

      <form action="/analyze" method="POST" class="container" id="analysis-form">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="source">Policy Source</label>
          <input 
            type="text" 
            id="source" 
            name="source" 
            required
            placeholder="e.g. Facebook"
          >
        </div>

        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="policy">Paste Privacy Policy Text</label>
          <textarea 
            id="policy" 
            name="policy" 
            rows="15" 
            required
            placeholder="Copy and paste the privacy policy text here..."
          ></textarea>
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="analyze-button">Analyze Policy</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <script>
    const textarea = document.getElementById('policy');
    const form = document.querySelector('.analysis-form');
    
    form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
      const text = textarea.value.trim();
      if (text.length < 100) {
        e.preventDefault();
        alert('Please paste at least 100 characters');
      }
    });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
